OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772730673
OL,3,CHaboobs and 'blood rain': Britain's
OL,4,Cskies to ignite with intense, fiery
OL,5,Csunsets
OL,7,FThe word 'haboob' comes from the
OL,8,FArabic 'habub', which literally
OL,9,Ftranslates to 'blasting' or 'strong
OL,10,Fwind' and it refers to an intense
OL,11,Fdesert dust or sand storm.
OL,13,FThe dramatic walls of dust and sand
OL,14,Fthat the haboob creates stay in desert
OL,15,Fregions, but the very finest particles
OL,16,Fare carried high into the atmosphere
OL,17,Fand then transported on currents of
OL,18,Fair high up in the atmosphere over
OL,19,Fgreat distances, eventually reaching
OL,20,Four skies and beyond.
OL,26,@pD@Luz
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
