OL,3,CHaboobs and 'blood rain': Britain's
OL,4,Cskies to ignite with intense, fiery
OL,5,Csunsets
OL,7,FThe most vibrant colours tend to
OL,8,Fappear when skies are clear at sunrise
OL,9,Fand sunset. So if you're up early or
OL,10,Fheading home as the sun dips, take a
OL,11,Fmoment to look up.
OL,13,FThese sights are a wonderful reminder
OL,14,Fthat our weather is connected to a
OL,15,Fmuch bigger global picture. Those
OL,16,Fbeautiful colours in the skies above
OL,17,Four homes are the result of weather
OL,18,Fsystems thousands of miles away - and
OL,19,FI think that's pretty amazing.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
